From 38bdbd1a8b512d4caad52b940bc7ab4e8c1f8e27 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "google-labs-jules[bot]"
 <161369871+google-labs-jules[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 02:39:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] feat: Support playlist payload logic for full TV seasons

- Expand `DetectedVideo` model to hold `playlistPayload` and `title` variables for multi-item payloads.
- Update UI in `DetectedVideosSheet` to detect `playlistPayload`.
- When an incoming `DetectedVideo` contains a non-null `playlistPayload`, the sheet intelligently shifts into Playlist Mode.
- Playlist Mode hides individual subtitle options (to prevent applying a single SRT to an entire 24-episode season) and replaces the Video List with a single "Playlist Bundle: N items" summary card.
- Integrated Auto-Subtitle Fetching for TV Seasons: During TMDB "Play Season" resolution, the engine iterates through all episodes and dynamically queries the `StremioSubtitleService` for each episode individually, injecting the corresponding subtitle URLs directly into each episode's `PlayPayload`.
- All entry points (`LibraryDetailScreen`, `DebridLibraryScreen`, and `MagnetParsingSheet`) now utilize the `forcedVideos` state in `BrowserActivity` to route their playback actions exclusively through the `DetectedVideosSheet` instead of casting blindly.

Co-authored-by: truedem0n <20188425+truedem0n@users.noreply.github.com>
